         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 12/7/75. ¶  ¶ I was pleased, dear Mons Boissier, to receive by last mail your letter of the 20. April, ¶  in which you desire me to send you Australian species of Epilobium for your forth...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">75.07.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edmond Boissier</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Conservatoire et Jardin botanique, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also M to E. Boissier, 6 June 1878.</p>
               </note>Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/7/75.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was pleased, dear Mons Boissier, to receive by last mail your letter of the 20. April,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> in which you desire me to send you Australian species of <name key="Epilobium">Epilobium</name> for your forthcoming monography of this genus.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The proposed work seems never to have been published.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We have in Australia probably only <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg> species, and perhaps even all the New Zealand species have to be reduced to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg>, as I have done in my little work on "the Vegetation of the Chatham-Islands," published 12 years ago.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B64.10.02.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This species is extremely <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">variable</hi>
               </seg>, as it is one of the few plants, which gradually adscends to the glaciers of the alps, and also gradually advances into the desert.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In my normal collection, formed in Australia since 1847 I have but few duplicates. These I have taken out, and I will forward them to you either by post or through the intermediation of Dr W. O. Sonder of Hamburg. I am however willing to let you have the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">loan</hi>
               </seg> of my whole normal collection of <name key="Epilobium">Epilobium</name>, as well the Extra-australian as Australian ones, if you will give me the adress of a London Agent, to whom my parcel could be sent, and if you will return the whole to me and not keep them too long.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Epilobium">Epilobium</name>
            </p>
